{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5ebd8141-e75b-4b59-bfaf-cfa3caf5ea45","content":"The issue is classic F#: **file compilation order matters**. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on types defined in `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear earlier in the compilation list.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_JLpfSNsiV6I6dsJFcdj35a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5d01c36bb8bb4e559358de0a1da11506/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5d01c36bb8bb4e559358de0a1da11506/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"faa40d10-bd23-453c-a145-b28a1c4af6ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the `.fsproj` file. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order`, `OrderId` types)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\n\nThe fix is straightforward: I need to reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":425,"requestId":"0411:2A854:43092A:4E5681:69F00427"},"id":"c08ce809-e285-49e4-a757-5528068aa2f5","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:51.229Z","parentId":"764a73c2-4aae-441b-aae2-4a224d4fa469"}
